TITLE Prefer Composing Children Over Render Props
PREFER CHILDREN OVER RENDER PROPS
Use children for composition IO renderX props. Children are more readable, compose naturally, and don't require understanding callback signatures. 
Incorrect (render props): 
CODE tsx 605CHARS
Correct (compound components with children): 
CODE tsx 473CHARS
When render props are appropriate: 
CODE tsx 153CHARS
Use render props when the parent needs to provide data or state to the child. Use children when composing static structure. 